$interpreted: Purple-Cloak: Wah! You've come this far where others have failed.
Federal Officer: You've been using a bunch of idiots to drag me along. Come on now!
Purple-Cloak: Very insightful of you. How about a little reward? I'll tell you what my goal is.
Federal Officer: Not interested, hand over the Bunny Blooms.
Purple-Cloak: Oh~ is it time for the criminal to confess? What do you say, Miss Assistant?
Assistant: I'm sorry, but I'm not interested.
Purple-Cloak: ......
Assistant: ......
Purple-Cloak: Come on! Good cop, bad cop! You ought to be different from the big guy. I'll give you another chance.
Assistant: No problem. Hand over the Bunny Blooms and your life~
Purple-Cloak: Wait a sec! What'd you say? My life!?
Federal Officer: Are you as stupid as your friends? You can't trust a scumbag like her.
Federal Officer: Hey useless piece of junk, what are you doing?
Assistant: It's not clear~ My disgust detection software suddenly self-activated.
Federal Officer: I've had enough of you! I'm gonna destroy you right now!
Purple-Cloak: ...HELLO! The bad guy's over here...
Purple-Cloak: ...what I meant was...
Purple-Cloak: ...if you'd listen to what I'm saying...
Purple-Cloak: Enough! If you keep this up you're gonna destroy the wild Bunny Blooms.
Federal Officer: Huh? The species that grows in the wild is already extinct...!
Federal Officer: No, this can't be. They really are wild Bunny Blooms.
Purple-Cloak: That's right. They're the only ones left...
Assistant: The Bunny Blooms are lighting up!
Assistant: Bunny Bloom incarnate???????
Spirit of Bunny Bloom: Oh, did I scare you? Your expression is priceless. I'd pay a lot of money for it.
Spirit of Bunny Bloom: Come, now~ let's share a dance before the moonlight comes in its brightest splendor~
Spirit of Bunny Bloom: *sigh*...lost again~
Federal Officer: So all you wanted to do was to protect these wild fruits. But why drag us along?
Spirit of Bunny Bloom: The full moon has finally arrived.
Federal Officer: Full moon? There's no way that you're...
Spirit of Bunny Bloom: Actually, Bunny Blooms were originally a gift for you people.
Spirit of Bunny Bloom: But mankind...*sigh*...you kept harvesting them excessively, with seemingly limitless desire. With no concept of moderation, you nearly made these poor children go extinct.
Spirit of Bunny Bloom: So I must take them all back home.
Spirit of Bunny Bloom: However, this was quite fun. We'll come back to play when we get the chance~
Assistant: ── Target disappeared. Reason, unable to comprehend.
Federal Officer: ...The spirit of the Bunny Bloom? Not at all what I expected.
Assistant: How are we going to explain this to the nobles?
Federal Officer: Those blockheads can eat artificially flavored food for all I care. As for the gift of the full moon. Well, it's already returned from where it came.
Assistant: ──that's right, it's all wrapped up……understood, I believe that he will enjoy it.
Federal Officer: Wh-what are you doing cooking here?
Security Minister: The report said you did very well, so I came specifically to give you a little reward.
Federal Officer: I'm warning you...don't come any closer!!
Federal Officer: Stop...NO...get awayyy!!!!
